		<IRequirement type="e">
			<_id type="a">GUID ff16242c-e43a-453b-a998-e29b989584ad</_id>
			<_myState type="a">8192</_myState>
			<_name type="a">Collision Detection</_name>
			<_modifiedTimeWeak type="a">1.2.1990::0:0:0</_modifiedTimeWeak>
			<_description type="p"><IDescription type="e">
				<_text type="a">Collision detection%0D
Collision detection should take place in each period (interation) of the gate movement and consists in counting by the infrared receiver the pulses sent by the infrared transmitter.%0D
1. If the number of pulses received and sent differ significantly, send an appropriate signal to the Controller, which should stop the drive%0D
2.Otherwise, keep moving.</_text>
			</IDescription>
			</_description>
			<_modifiedTime type="a">6.2.2026::10:33:29</_modifiedTime>
			<_body type="a">{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1250\deff0\deflang1045{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset238{\*\fname Arial;}Arial CE;}}%0D
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 Collision detection\par%0D
Collision detection should take place in each period (interation) of the gate movement and consists in counting by the infrared receiver the pulses sent by the infrared transmitter.\par%0D
1. If the number of pulses received and sent differ significantly, send an appropriate signal to the Controller, which should stop the drive\par%0D
2.Otherwise, keep moving.\par%0D
}%0D
</_body>
		</IRequirement>
		<IRequirement type="e">
			<_id type="a">GUID b1338eb1-9d83-43f0-832e-12615a3a6984</_id>
